reviewText:
Forget the general critics from God of ♥♥♥♥♥" and "Symphony of the Night" fans (the majority of them just played SOTN and dont really knows about Castlevania games at all) this is a deep very well made fan service.

Rule of the tumb: if you liked the 1st Castlevania: Lords of Shadow this game is a "Instabuy"

***Edited at 09/13/14 to review the DLC Revelations.***

PROS:
- Improved combat and movement mechanics making this even more solid;
- Awesome graphics and immersive scenarios (combine several aspects of Vampire lore with Castlevania's elements);
- Free movement camera;
- Lots of extra content including: 400 pages of design artwork (seems much but it is easy to have those collected during the game - I've completed mine in the 1st run)

date:
 Challenges and Lore
- Fantastic follow up history;
- About 14~17 hours long (if you're a completionist and like achievements you would mostly at least double that time);
- On LOS1 the platforming wasn't really great and you finished get killed by bad jumping several times. That was corrected!


CONS:
- Although stealth isn't that bad as people say (in reality just a puzzle) it is so easy that doesn't adds any value to the gameplay at all;
- In 17 hours -my 1st run- I didnt spend no more than 30 minutes with ALL puzzles (including stealth) which means that the puzzles are super easy. The LOS1 puzzles were waaaaay more fun;
- Voice acting

reviewText:
Simply the BEST Action-Adventure ever made!

This game improves all the good things of the first Chapter, and corrects all the bad things about Castlevania Lords of Shadow. The Metacritic medium rank, 5,8/10, is simply ridiculous; I think that it deserves a full 10/10.

The good:
- awesome graphics, much better then in Castlevania 1 and with fluider animations;
- excellent gameplay (and, this time, with a mobile camera);
- the BEST Boss battles ever made;
- wonderful environments, a bit less various then in Castlevania 1 but even more beautiful;
- you start as a villain, and finish recovering your humanity.

The bad: there isn't anything wrong about this game.

In conclusion, for me this game is far better then the first chapter and I can't really understand the reason why videogame critics have judged it so badly.
